# Kapso Safety

Use Kapso's CLI for source-controlled workflow work and Kapso MCP for live project inspection when it is authenticated.

Classify operations before acting:

- Read-only: status, list, get, resolve, health checks, docs search, build, pull, and dry-run commands.
- Local writes: source files, validation reports, sample payloads, and local workflow/function edits.
- High-risk writes: `kapso push`, message sends, template changes, webhook changes, function deploys, trigger changes, customer/setup-link changes, and destructive operations.

Ask for explicit user approval before high-risk writes. Prefer `kapso build` and `kapso push --dry-run` before a real deploy.
